    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>
                <add>Hebrew</add>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <hi rend="underline">Kalid.</hi>
            </p>
            <p>With the help of God, blessed be He</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">To the princes and officers of the cities of<lb/>
                <placeName>America</placeName>, may God bless you, etc.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">After extending our greeting to you, I<lb/> want to let you know
                that some time ago<lb/> I announced ot all the lands that which I<lb/> have done in
                order that Jews might have a livelihood<lb/> from farming and manual labor in the
                    <placeName>holy land</placeName>.<lb/> For, as our sages said, "All the artisans
                are <del>dest</del><lb/> destined to arise, etc.", As a result I have<lb/> had great
                heartache and financial loss, and I<lb/> requested of you that you send us one
                gift*. Dur-<lb/>ing the past year, however, all my mules died,<lb/> and everything
                was almost lost. For I did not have<lb/> enough capital to purchase mules and to
                work the<lb/> sail. But God provided us with <del>a way of escape</del>
                deliverance<lb/> through the <persName>Signora Mrs. Monni Campanile</persName>,<lb/>
                who lives here in the <placeName>holy land</placeName> and is engaged<lb/> in
                agriculture by employing Israelites who gain<lb/> a livelihood through her. She also
                did me this<lb/> kindness and paid for everything from her own<lb/> pocket, so as to
                enable me to work the soil at present.</p>
            <p>* I cannot understand the nature<lb/> of this gift. It is either a gift of a<lb/>
                tool <del>
                    <add>?</add>
                </del> or a sum of money.</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>Nevertheless, money is still necessary to<lb/> complete all the buildings and other
                needed ex-<lb/>penses. And now I come with this request<lb/> that you have mercy
                upon us and upon our<lb/> land and our in-<sic>heritance</sic>, so that through<lb/>
                you and through her we might succeed, and<lb/> many other families of our
                fellow-Israelites should<lb/> gain a livelihood. If you desire, let us<lb/> know,
                and we shall send you from the fruit of<lb/> the <placeName>holy land</placeName>
                ethrogim, Kosher and beautiful,<lb/>which are grown in our orchards, and by the<lb/>
                hand of Israelites. Thus will you be<lb/> privileged to utter your benedictions and
                to fulfill<lb/> your commandments with regard to the fruit of<lb/> the
                    <placeName>holy land</placeName>. We look forward to your reply<lb/> and I
                remain, with a greeting of peace, he<lb/> who prays for your good fortune
                forever.<lb/> Signed in the <placeName>Holy Land</placeName>,
                    <placeName>Jaffa</placeName>, <date>Adar, 1854</date>.</p>
            <p><persName role="author">Raphael Judah</persName>, Son of <persName>Menachem<lb/>
                    Halevy</persName>, community leader<lb/> in the <placeName>Holy
                Land</placeName></p>
